This investment consists of extension the new 400 kV substation Ladce, in order to loop 400 kV cross-border OHL from Ladce (SK) to Otrokovice (CZ). The new 400 kV substation Ladce will replace existing 220 kV substation Považská Bystrica and will therefore increase security of supply in this particular region. After commissioning this new 400 kV substation it will be possible to commission new 400 kV cross-border OHL from Ladce (SK) to Otrokovice (CZ).
